As we celebrate this weekend, let us follow Rep. Hollin’s advice and talk about history with our families—let’s recognize the heroes from the past and consider the bright future we can build together.
I commend my friend and former colleague, Rep. @SHollinsD21, on the passage of her bill recognizing Juneteenth as a state holiday here in Utah.
As Rev. Martin Luther King said, “Our goal is to create a beloved community and this will require a qualitative change in our souls as well as a quantitative change in our lives.”
The commemoration of this event is an important step to making everyone feel included in our community and in our future.

I loved joining so many Utahns at the Utah Juneteenth Heritage Festival in Ogden as we came together to celebrate the emancipation of enslaved African Americans in the United States. https://t.co/ckU7rKkx59
